args: As you know, Highness, I agreed to wear\nthis outfit for the sake of our operation.
However, I cannot help but feel gloomy\nthinking what would happen if someone\nfrom the Church saw me like this.
Why would the Church be concerned\nwith you wearing a wedding dress?
We Paladyns are not allowed to marry\nwithout the Church's permission.

First, we must secure parental approval.
Then there is an inquiry to determine if our
love is genuine, after which a high Church
official must give their formal consent.
There are also countless procedures that\nneed to be followed and oaths to swear—\nfar more than for an ordinary layman.
Marriage is a highly sacred and solemn\nmatter for Paladyns, and one we do not\ntake lightly.
Sounds like a real gauntlet\nof sufferin' right there.
When taking up our position, we swear\nto devote our hearts and bodies entirely\nto Ilia and the people of this land.
All of which amounts to yet another reason\nI do not feel comfortable in this frock.
Yeah, but yer just wearin' the dress to\nfool some fiend! Ain't like yer actually\ngonna be dodgin' rice in the aisle.
Indeed, you are doing this to protect\ninnocent lives. You should be proud.

(And yet, it is difficult NOT to think about
marriage while wearing a dress like this.
And it's not as though I've never dreamed
of doing such a thing...)
(But the Church's decision in these matters\nis final. If they withhold their approval,\nthere is nothing that can be done.)
(Augh, no! What am I even thinking?\nI could never put His Highness through\nsomething like that!)
(...Wait. Why did HE come into this?!)
(The issue of marriage is difficult enough\nbetween members of the Church, never\nmind between a Paladyn and a royal.)

(Although come to think of it, I am unsure
if such a thing has ever come to pass.
I would be generating an entirely new
problem for the Church to puzzle out!)
(If it were to result in a factional schism,\nI would be dragging His Highness into\nthe center of yet another conflict!)
(...Augh! WHY does his name\nkeep coming up in this?!)
(How shameful. I dedicated myself to Ilia,\nyet now find myself adrift in fantasy.)

(This needs to end! I must remember the
oath I took when becoming a Paladyn—
the one where I swore to stand up to
hardship and evil no matter the cost!)
(...But if it came to it, I'm sure he would\nfight by my side so long as our love for\none another burned bright.)
You okay, Elly? You've been muttering\nto yourself for a while now.
There is no obstacle too great\nfor love to overcome!
Yes, love! ...Wait, no! What am I saying?!
Sorry, I'm sort of confused. When did the\npower of love come into all of this?
I meant...um...my love for the goddess!\nYes, that's it. So long as I hold Ilia in my\nheart, there is no trial I cannot overcome!
I was just trying to motivate myself to face\nthe task ahead, as any true Paladyn might!\nAh ha! Ah ha ha...haaaaaaaa.
Oh! Well, I suppose that makes sense.
At any rate, let's make sure this mission\nis a rousing success, Elly!
(Ugh. How could I possibly let vice\nconsume me like this?)
(I am a Paladyn! My mind should be free\nof all such immoral thoughts!)
Ah, hell! Look at all of 'em!
I don't think they're related to the fiend\nthat's threatening the village—but that\ndoesn't mean we can ignore them!
You can leave this to us, Elly.\nYou can't fight in that dre—
...A Paladyn. A PALADYN!\nI AM A PALADYYYYYYN!
Well, she's certainly making\nshort work of this bunch.
I can only assume it's a result of how\nvery unforgivable she finds all this.\nShe really IS a model Paladyn.
Yeah, I don't think that's it, boss.
For once, I actually agree with Ranzal.\n...I may need to go lie down.
